item.title: [+1072] Haitian Farmers Commit to Burning Monsanto Seeds
item.description: The Peasant Movement of Papay called the news that Monsanto will be donating 60,000 seed sacks (475 tons) of hybrid corn seeds and vegetable seeds a "new earthquake". The MPP has committed to burning Monsanto's seeds, and has called for a march to protest the corporation's presence in Haiti on June 4, for World Environment Day.
